X
\rho
E[X] = 1/\rho
E[X^2] = (1-\rho)/(\rho)^2
E[X^c] \leq O(1/\rho^c)
k\geqslant1
X^k
X(X-1)\cdots(X-i+1)
i\leqslant k
C_k
k
s=1
 E(X(X-1)\cdots(X-k+1))=\frac{k!\,(1-\varrho)^{k-1}}{\varrho^k}\leqslant\frac{k!}{\varrho^k}, 
 E(X^k)\leqslant\frac{C_k}{\varrho^k}, 
 E(s^X)=\sum_{i=1}^\infty \varrho(1-\varrho)^{i-1}s^i=\frac{\varrho s}{1-(1-\varrho)s}=\frac{\varrho}{1-\varrho}\,\left(\frac1{1-(1-\varrho)s}-1\right). 
